      "date": "2018-07-13 16:57:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nJust FYI, there was no need to resubmit the patch if it had already passed testing previously. The \"trivial\" keyword is useful for patches that only affect code style or test scripts (it runs sanity and lnet-selftest only, unless other tests are added with the \"test list=\" keyword. \n\nThe patch is OK as-is, but if it needs to be refreshed for some other reason then the minor improvements can be made.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1e1614619a5cd00c3a5a6502ab6ab869a9525bd8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2018-07-19 09:07:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nWe use \"pkill -x\" to kill copytools at the end of tests. The man page of pkill states: \"The process name used for matching is limited to the 15 characters present in the output of /proc/pid/stat.\"\n\nWhile this is not an issue for lhsmtool_posix (14 chars), it is for lt-lhsmtool_posix. =D",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4d6dd31e761f1e210e9e4f2f464784021edb6375",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2018-07-19 14:03:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nActually I found the solution to this problem. Add \"lhsmtool_posix_LDFLAGS = -no-install\" to the Makefile in lustre/utils and libtools will not create a exectuable wrapper.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
